	  values have VALUE type. there is an environment where sizeof(VALUE)
	  != sizeof(int) like IA64. if 32bit integer (Qtrue) is passed to ANYARGS
	  and received by 64bit integer (VALUE), upper bits may have garbage value.
	  [ruby-dev:27513]

